<h2>It's as simple as A B C</h2>

Notes are encoded with letters and numbers.  Special commands are
entered with backslashes.

<p align="center">

  <img src="..//graphics/annotate-example-1"
       alt="annotate-example-1">
  <br>
  <img src="../images/example-1" alt="example-1"> 

<p>
  Alterations are made with different names: add -is for sharp,
and -es
  for flat (these are Dutch note names, other languages are
  available).  LilyPond figures out where to put accidentals.
</p>

<p align="center">
  <img src="..//graphics/annotate-example-2"
       alt="annotate-example-2">
  <br>
  <img src="../images/example-2" alt="example-2">

</p>

