<h2>Orchestral parts</h2>

<p>
  <a name="orchestral"></a> The input file contains the notes of
  piece. Score and parts can be made from a single input file. So,
  changing a note always affects both parts and score. To  share
the
  notes, the music is assigned to a variable:
</p>

<p align="center">
  <img src="..//graphics/annotate-example-parts"
       alt="annotate-example-parts">
  <br>
</p>

<p>
  This variable is then used in a single part (here transposed,
with
  condensed multi rests):
</p>

<p align="center">
  <img src="..//graphics/annotate-example-single-part"
       alt="annotate-example-single-part">
  <br>
  <img src="../images/example-singlepart"
alt="example-singlepart">
</p>

<p>
  The same variable is used in the full score (here in concert
pitch):

</p>

<p align="center">
  <img src="..//graphics/annotate-example-score"
       alt="annotate-example-score">
  <br>
  <img src="../images/example-score" alt="example-score">
</p>


